{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:john.10",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "john",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "John 10",
    "summary": "Source text for John 10 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:1",
      "text": "“Truly, truly, I say to you, he who does not enter the sheepfold by the door but climbs in by another way, that man is a thief and a robber;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:2",
      "text": "but he who enters by the door is the shepherd of the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:3",
      "text": "To him the gatekeeper opens; the sheep hear his voice, and he calls his own sheep by name and leads them out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:4",
      "text": "When he has brought out all his own, he goes before them, and the sheep follow him, for they know his voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:5",
      "text": "A stranger they will not follow, but they will flee from him, for they do not know the voice of strangers.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:6",
      "text": "This figure Jesus used with them, but they did not understand what he was saying to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:7",
      "text": "So Jesus again said to them, “Truly, truly, I say to you, I am the door of the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:8",
      "text": "All who came before me are thieves and robbers; but the sheep did not heed them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:9",
      "text": "I am the door; if any one enters by me, he will be saved, and will go in and out and find pasture.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:10",
      "text": "The thief comes only to steal and kill and destroy; I came that they may have life, and have it abundantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:11",
      "text": "I am the good shepherd. The good shepherd lays down his life for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:12",
      "text": "He who is a hireling and not a shepherd, whose own the sheep are not, sees the wolf coming and leaves the sheep and flees; and the wolf snatches them and scatters them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:13",
      "text": "He flees because he is a hireling and cares nothing for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:14",
      "text": "I am the good shepherd; I know my own and my own know me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:15",
      "text": "as the Father knows me and I know the Father; and I lay down my life for the sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:16",
      "text": "And I have other sheep, that are not of this fold; I must bring them also, and they will heed my voice. So there shall be one flock, one shepherd.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:17",
      "text": "For this reason the Father loves me, because I lay down my life, that I may take it again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:18",
      "text": "No one takes it from me, but I lay it down of my own accord. I have power to lay it down, and I have power to take it again; this charge I have received from my Father.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:19",
      "text": "There was again a division among the Jews because of these words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:20",
      "text": "Many of them said, “He has a demon, and he is mad; why listen to him?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:21",
      "text": "Others said, “These are not the sayings of one who has a demon. Can a demon open the eyes of the blind?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:22",
      "text": "It was the feast of the Dedication at Jerusalem;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:23",
      "text": "it was winter, and Jesus was walking in the temple, in the portico of Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:24",
      "text": "So the Jews gathered round him and said to him, “How long will you keep us in suspense? If you are the Christ, tell us plainly.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:25",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, “I told you, and you do not believe. The works that I do in my Father's name, they bear witness to me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:26",
      "text": "but you do not believe, because you do not belong to my sheep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:27",
      "text": "My sheep hear my voice, and I know them, and they follow me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:28",
      "text": "and I give them eternal life, and they shall never perish, and no one shall snatch them out of my hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:29",
      "text": "My Father, who has given them to me, is greater than all, and no one is able to snatch them out of the Father's hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:30",
      "text": "I and the Father are one.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:31",
      "text": "The Jews took up stones again to stone him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:32",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, “I have shown you many good works from the Father; for which of these do you stone me?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:33",
      "text": "The Jews answered him, “It is not for a good work that we stone you but for blasphemy; because you, being a man, make yourself God.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:34",
      "text": "Jesus answered them, “Is it not written in your law, ‘I said, you are gods’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:35",
      "text": "If he called them gods to whom the word of God came (and scripture cannot be broken),",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:36",
      "text": "do you say of him whom the Father consecrated and sent into the world, ‘You are blaspheming,’ because I said, ‘I am the Son of God’?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:37",
      "text": "If I am not doing the works of my Father, then do not believe me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:38",
      "text": "but if I do them, even though you do not believe me, believe the works, that you may know and understand that the Father is in me and I am in the Father.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:39",
      "text": "Again they tried to arrest him, but he escaped from their hands.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:40",
      "text": "He went away again across the Jordan to the place where John at first baptized, and there he remained.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:41",
      "text": "And many came to him; and they said, “John did no sign, but everything that John said about this man was true.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:john.10.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "john",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "John 10:42",
      "text": "And many believed in him there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
